cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language modelling. The use of deep neural networks and stochastic modelling also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of Monte Carlo sampling suggests that it could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as this is a common technique used in software testing. Finally, the use of hybridization to improve the performance of the models suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
